column1: -# The results of running CIAlign on the QuanTest2 test alignments and the impact of CIAlign on the percentage similarity in protein secondary structure between the QuanTest2 reference sequences and the test alignments
-# CIAlign_Stringency: parameter settings as listed in Supplementary Table 1 (None means without running CIAlign)

-# QuanTest2_Percentage_Similarity: mean percentage similarity between the reference secondary structure and the secondary structure calculated from the reference sequences in the test alignment, calcualted with QuanTest2
# Original_Length: number of columns in the alignment before running CIAlign
# CIAlign_Length: number of columns in the alignment after running CIAlign
# Percentage_Original_Length: CIAlign length as a proportion of Original_Length

# Original_Perc_Correct_Positions_Median - Median percentage similarity between the reference secondary structure and the secondary structure calculated from the reference sequences in the test alignment, calculated with QuanTest2

# CIAlign_Perc_Correct_Positions_Median: Median percentage similarity between the reference secondary structure and the secondary structure calculated from the reference sequences in the test alignment cleaned with CIAlign, calculated with QuanTest2.
# CIAlign_Change_Correct_Positions_Median: Difference between Original_Perc_Correct_Positions_Median and CIAlign_Perc_Correct_Positions_Median as a percentage
